

PPT Summary — Dashboard Design for Business Stakeholders


Slide 1 — Title Slide

Title: Dashboard Design for Business Stakeholders

Subtitle: Data Analyst Internship – Task 4

Arathy Krishna S | Data Analyst Intern


Slide 2 — Project Overview

Goal: Create an interactive dashboard to track Sales, Profit, and Growth.

Tools Used: Power BI / Tableau, Excel / Python.

Dataset: Kaggle Sales Dataset (fields: Date, Region, Sales Amount, Profit, Category).


Slide 3 — Dataset Details

Source: Kaggle Sales/Financial dataset.

Type: Sales transaction data.

Purpose: Provide actionable insights for business decision-making.


Slide 4 — KPIs Tracked

Total Sales.

Total Profit.

Growth Rate (%).

Monthly Trends.


Slide 5 — Dashboard Features

Slicers & Filters for Date, Region, Category.

Time-Series Charts for trend analysis.

Card visuals for KPIs.

Consistent color scheme for readability.

Optional navigation menu for better UX.


Slide 6 — How to Use the Dashboard

1. Open .pbix (Power BI) or .twb (Tableau) file.


2. Connect to dataset if prompted.


3. Use slicers to filter data.


4. Review KPI cards and visual charts for insights.


Slide 7 — Conclusion

Interactive dashboards enable real-time insights.

Helps stakeholders make data-driven decisions.




